$ cquad4_axial_force.bdf
$ Single CQUAD4 axial extension — plane stress
$
$ Geometry: 1 m × 1 m square plate, t = 0.1 m
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3
$ Load:     1000 N total in +x, applied as 500 N at each right-edge node
$ BCs:      minimal — fix T1 of left-edge nodes (no T1 rigid body),
$           fix T2 of node 1 (no T2 rigid body / rotation)
$
$ Hand calculation (exact for bilinear CQUAD4):
$   A = h * t = 1 * 0.1 = 0.1 m²
$   δ = F*L / (E*A) = 1000*1 / (1e6*0.1) = 0.01 m
$   σ_x = F / A = 10000 Pa  (with σ_y = 0, free Poisson contraction)
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = AXIAL FORCE
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
$ Nodes: corners of 1x1 plate in the xy-plane
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
$ Material
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3
$ Shell property: t = 0.1 m
PSHELL,1,1,0.1
$ Single CQUAD4 element (CCW node order viewed from +z)
CQUAD4,1,1,1,2,3,4
$ BCs: fix T1 of nodes 1 and 4 (left edge); fix T2 of node 1
SPC1,1,1,1
SPC1,1,1,4
SPC1,1,2,1
$ Loads: 500 N in +x at each right-edge node
FORCE,1,2,0,500.0,1.0,0.0,0.0
FORCE,1,3,0,500.0,1.0,0.0,0.0
ENDDATA
